var book = {
	"name": "Judges",
	"numChapters": 21,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>After the death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6511B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6511B\"></sup> of Joshua, the Israelites asked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Who of us is to go up first<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6511C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6511C\"></sup> to fight against the Canaanites?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6511D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6511D\"></sup>”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered, “Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6512E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6512E\"></sup> shall go up; I have given the land into their hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6512F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6512F\"></sup>”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The men of Judah then said to the Simeonites their fellow Israelites, “Come up with us into the territory allotted to us, to fight against the Canaanites. We in turn will go with you into yours.” So the Simeonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6513G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6513G\"></sup> went with them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When Judah attacked, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave the Canaanites and Perizzites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6514H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6514H\"></sup> into their hands, and they struck down ten thousand men at Bezek.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6514I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6514I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It was there that they found Adoni-Bezek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6515J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6515J\"></sup> and fought against him, putting to rout the Canaanites and Perizzites.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Adoni-Bezek fled, but they chased him and caught him, and cut off his thumbs and big toes.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Adoni-Bezek said, “Seventy kings with their thumbs and big toes cut off have picked up scraps under my table. Now God has paid me back<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6517K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6517K\"></sup> for what I did to them.” They brought him to Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6517L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6517L\"></sup> and he died there.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The men of Judah attacked Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6518M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6518M\"></sup> also and took it. They put the city to the sword and set it on fire.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After that, Judah went down to fight against the Canaanites living in the hill country,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6519N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6519N\"></sup> the Negev<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6519O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6519O\"></sup> and the western foothills.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They advanced against the Canaanites living in Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6520P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6520P\"></sup> (formerly called Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6520Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6520Q\"></sup>) and defeated Sheshai, Ahiman and Talmai.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6520R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6520R\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>From there they advanced against the people living in Debir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6521S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6521S\"></sup> (formerly called Kiriath Sepher).",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Caleb said, “I will give my daughter Aksah in marriage to the man who attacks and captures Kiriath Sepher.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Othniel son of Kenaz, Caleb’s younger brother, took it; so Caleb gave his daughter Aksah to him in marriage.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>One day when she came to Othniel, she urged him to ask her father for a field. When she got off her donkey, Caleb asked her, “What can I do for you?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>She replied, “Do me a special favor. Since you have given me land in the Negev, give me also springs of water.” So Caleb gave her the upper and lower springs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6525T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6525T\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The descendants of Moses’ father-in-law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6526U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6526U\"></sup> the Kenite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6526V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6526V\"></sup> went up from the City of Palms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6526W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6526W\"></sup> with the people of Judah to live among the inhabitants of the Desert of Judah in the Negev near Arad.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6526X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6526X\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the men of Judah went with the Simeonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6527Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6527Y\"></sup> their fellow Israelites and attacked the Canaanites living in Zephath, and they totally destroyed the city. Therefore it was called Hormah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6527Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6527Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Judah also took Gaza,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6528AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6528AA\"></sup> Ashkelon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6528AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6528AB\"></sup> and Ekron—each city with its territory.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6529AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6529AC\"></sup> the men of Judah. They took possession of the hill country,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6529AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6529AD\"></sup> but they were unable to drive the people from the plains, because they had chariots fitted with iron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6529AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6529AE\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As Moses had promised, Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6530AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6530AF\"></sup> was given to Caleb, who drove from it the three sons of Anak.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6530AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6530AG\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The Benjamites, however, did not drive out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6531AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6531AH\"></sup> the Jebusites, who were living in Jerusalem;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6531AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6531AI\"></sup> to this day the Jebusites live there with the Benjamites.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now the tribes of Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6532AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6532AJ\"></sup> attacked Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6532AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6532AK\"></sup> and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When they sent men to spy out Bethel (formerly called Luz),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6533AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6533AL\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>the spies saw a man coming out of the city and they said to him, “Show us how to get into the city and we will see that you are treated well.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6534AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6534AM\"></sup>”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So he showed them, and they put the city to the sword but spared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6535AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6535AN\"></sup> the man and his whole family.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He then went to the land of the Hittites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6536AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6536AO\"></sup> where he built a city and called it Luz,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6536AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6536AP\"></sup> which is its name to this day.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Manasseh did not<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6537AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6537AQ\"></sup> drive out the people of Beth Shan or Taanach or Dor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6537AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6537AR\"></sup> or Ibleam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6537AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6537AS\"></sup> or Megiddo<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6537AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6537AT\"></sup> and their surrounding settlements, for the Canaanites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6537AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6537AU\"></sup> were determined to live in that land.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When Israel became strong, they pressed the Canaanites into forced labor but never drove them out completely.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6538AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6538AV\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Nor did Ephraim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6539AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6539AW\"></sup> drive out the Canaanites living in Gezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6539AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6539AX\"></sup> but the Canaanites continued to live there among them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6539AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6539AY\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Neither did Zebulun drive out the Canaanites living in Kitron or Nahalol, so these Canaanites lived among them, but Zebulun did subject them to forced labor.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Nor did Asher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6541AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6541AZ\"></sup> drive out those living in Akko or Sidon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6541BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6541BA\"></sup> or Ahlab or Akzib<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6541BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6541BB\"></sup> or Helbah or Aphek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6541BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6541BC\"></sup> or Rehob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6541BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6541BD\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The Asherites lived among the Canaanite inhabitants of the land because they did not drive them out.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Neither did Naphtali drive out those living in Beth Shemesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6543BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6543BE\"></sup> or Beth Anath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6543BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6543BF\"></sup>; but the Naphtalites too lived among the Canaanite inhabitants of the land, and those living in Beth Shemesh and Beth Anath became forced laborers for them.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6544BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6544BG\"></sup> confined the Danites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6544BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6544BH\"></sup> to the hill country, not allowing them to come down into the plain.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6544BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6544BI\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And the Amorites were determined also to hold out in Mount Heres,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6545BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6545BJ\"></sup> Aijalon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6545BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6545BK\"></sup> and Shaalbim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6545BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6545BL\"></sup> but when the power of the tribes of Joseph increased, they too were pressed into forced labor.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The boundary of the Amorites was from Scorpion Pass<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6546BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6546BM\"></sup> to Sela<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6546BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6546BN\"></sup> and beyond.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6546BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6546BO\"></sup>"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6547A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6547A\"></sup> went up from Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6547B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6547B\"></sup> to Bokim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6547C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6547C\"></sup> and said, “I brought you up out of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6547D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6547D\"></sup> and led you into the land I swore to give to your ancestors.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6547E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6547E\"></sup> I said, ‘I will never break my covenant with you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6547F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6547F\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and you shall not make a covenant with the people of this land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6548G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6548G\"></sup> but you shall break down their altars.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6548H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6548H\"></sup>’ Yet you have disobeyed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6548I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6548I\"></sup> me. Why have you done this?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And I have also said, ‘I will not drive them out before you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6549J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6549J\"></sup> they will become traps<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6549K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6549K\"></sup> for you, and their gods will become snares<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6549L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6549L\"></sup> to you.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken these things to all the Israelites, the people wept aloud,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6550M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6550M\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and they called that place Bokim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6551N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6551N\"></sup> There they offered sacrifices to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After Joshua had dismissed the Israelites, they went to take possession of the land, each to their own inheritance.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The people served the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> throughout the lifetime of Joshua and of the elders who outlived him and who had seen all the great things the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done for Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6553P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6553P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Joshua son of Nun,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6554Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6554Q\"></sup> the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, died at the age of a hundred and ten.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And they buried him in the land of his inheritance, at Timnath Heres<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6555R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6555R\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim, north of Mount Gaash.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>After that whole generation had been gathered to their ancestors, another generation grew up who knew neither the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> nor what he had done for Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6556S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6556S\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the Israelites did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6557T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6557T\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6557U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6557U\"></sup> and served the Baals.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6557V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6557V\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They forsook the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors, who had brought them out of Egypt. They followed and worshiped various gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6558W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6558W\"></sup> of the peoples around them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6558X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6558X\"></sup> They aroused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6558Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6558Y\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6558Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6558Z\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>because they forsook<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6559AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6559AA\"></sup> him and served Baal and the Ashtoreths.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6559AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6559AB\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In his anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6560AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6560AC\"></sup> against Israel the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them into the hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6560AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6560AD\"></sup> of raiders who plundered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6560AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6560AE\"></sup> them. He sold them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6560AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6560AF\"></sup> into the hands of their enemies all around, whom they were no longer able to resist.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6560AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6560AG\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Whenever Israel went out to fight, the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was against them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6561AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6561AH\"></sup> to defeat them, just as he had sworn to them. They were in great distress.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6561AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6561AI\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up judges,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6562AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6562AJ\"></sup> who saved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6562AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6562AK\"></sup> them out of the hands of these raiders.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Yet they would not listen to their judges but prostituted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6563AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6563AL\"></sup> themselves to other gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6563AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6563AM\"></sup> and worshiped them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6563AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6563AN\"></sup> They quickly turned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6563AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6563AO\"></sup> from the ways of their ancestors, who had been obedient to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6563AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6563AP\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Whenever the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up a judge for them, he was with the judge and saved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6564AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6564AQ\"></sup> them out of the hands of their enemies as long as the judge lived; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> relented<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6564AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6564AR\"></sup> because of their groaning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6564AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6564AS\"></sup> under those who oppressed and afflicted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6564AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6564AT\"></sup> them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when the judge died, the people returned to ways even more corrupt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6565AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6565AU\"></sup> than those of their ancestors,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6565AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6565AV\"></sup> following other gods and serving and worshiping them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6565AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6565AW\"></sup> They refused to give up their evil practices and stubborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6565AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6565AX\"></sup> ways.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was very angry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6566AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6566AY\"></sup> with Israel and said, “Because this nation has violated the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6566AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6566AZ\"></sup> I ordained for their ancestors and has not listened to me,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I will no longer drive out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6567BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6567BA\"></sup> before them any of the nations Joshua left when he died.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I will use them to test<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6568BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6568BB\"></sup> Israel and see whether they will keep the way of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and walk in it as their ancestors did.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had allowed those nations to remain; he did not drive them out at once by giving them into the hands of Joshua.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6569BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6569BC\"></sup>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>These are the nations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> left to test<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6570A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6570A\"></sup> all those Israelites who had not experienced any of the wars in Canaan",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>(he did this only to teach warfare to the descendants of the Israelites who had not had previous battle experience):",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the five<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6572B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6572B\"></sup> rulers of the Philistines,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6572C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6572C\"></sup> all the Canaanites, the Sidonians, and the Hivites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6572D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6572D\"></sup> living in the Lebanon mountains from Mount Baal Hermon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6572E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6572E\"></sup> to Lebo Hamath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6572F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6572F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They were left to test<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6573G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6573G\"></sup> the Israelites to see whether they would obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands, which he had given their ancestors through Moses.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Israelites lived<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6574H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6574H\"></sup> among the Canaanites, Hittites, Amorites, Perizzites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6574I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6574I\"></sup> Hivites and Jebusites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6574J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6574J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They took their daughters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6575K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6575K\"></sup> in marriage and gave their own daughters to their sons, and served their gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6575L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6575L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Israelites did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; they forgot the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6576M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6576M\"></sup> their God and served the Baals and the Asherahs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6576N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6576N\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against Israel so that he sold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6577O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6577O\"></sup> them into the hands of Cushan-Rishathaim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6577P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6577P\"></sup> king of Aram Naharaim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6577Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6577Q\"></sup> to whom the Israelites were subject for eight years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But when they cried out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6578R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6578R\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he raised up for them a deliverer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6578S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6578S\"></sup> Othniel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6578T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6578T\"></sup> son of Kenaz, Caleb’s younger brother, who saved them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came on him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6579U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6579U\"></sup> so that he became Israel’s judge and went to war. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Cushan-Rishathaim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6579V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6579V\"></sup> king of Aram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6579W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6579W\"></sup> into the hands of Othniel, who overpowered him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the land had peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6580X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6580X\"></sup> for forty years,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6580Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6580Y\"></sup> until Othniel son of Kenaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6580Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6580Z\"></sup> died.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Again the Israelites did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6581AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6581AA\"></sup> and because they did this evil the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Eglon king of Moab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6581AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6581AB\"></sup> power over Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Getting the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6582AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6582AC\"></sup> and Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6582AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6582AD\"></sup> to join him, Eglon came and attacked Israel, and they took possession of the City of Palms.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6582AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6582AE\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Israelites were subject to Eglon king of Moab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6583AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6583AF\"></sup> for eighteen years.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Again the Israelites cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he gave them a deliverer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6584AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6584AG\"></sup>—Ehud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6584AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6584AH\"></sup>, a left-handed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6584AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6584AI\"></sup> man, the son of Gera the Benjamite. The Israelites sent him with tribute<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6584AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6584AJ\"></sup> to Eglon king of Moab.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now Ehud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6585AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6585AK\"></sup> had made a double-edged sword about a cubit long, which he strapped to his right thigh under his clothing.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He presented the tribute<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6586AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6586AL\"></sup> to Eglon king of Moab, who was a very fat man.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6586AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6586AM\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>After Ehud had presented the tribute, he sent on their way those who had carried it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But on reaching the stone images near Gilgal he himself went back to Eglon and said, “Your Majesty, I have a secret message for you.”The king said to his attendants, “Leave us!” And they all left.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Ehud then approached him while he was sitting alone in the upper room of his palace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6589AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6589AN\"></sup> and said, “I have a message from God for you.” As the king rose<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6589AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6589AO\"></sup> from his seat,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Ehud reached with his left hand, drew the sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6590AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6590AP\"></sup> from his right thigh and plunged it into the king’s belly.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Even the handle sank in after the blade, and his bowels discharged. Ehud did not pull the sword out, and the fat closed in over it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Ehud went out to the porch; he shut the doors of the upper room behind him and locked them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After he had gone, the servants came and found the doors of the upper room locked. They said, “He must be relieving himself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6593AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6593AQ\"></sup> in the inner room of the palace.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They waited to the point of embarrassment,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6594AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6594AR\"></sup> but when he did not open the doors of the room, they took a key and unlocked them. There they saw their lord fallen to the floor, dead.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>While they waited, Ehud got away. He passed by the stone images and escaped to Seirah.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When he arrived there, he blew a trumpet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6596AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6596AS\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim, and the Israelites went down with him from the hills, with him leading them.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Follow me,” he ordered, “for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given Moab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6597AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6597AT\"></sup> your enemy, into your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6597AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6597AU\"></sup>” So they followed him down and took possession of the fords of the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6597AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6597AV\"></sup> that led to Moab; they allowed no one to cross over.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>At that time they struck down about ten thousand Moabites, all vigorous and strong; not one escaped.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>That day Moab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6599AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6599AW\"></sup> was made subject to Israel, and the land had peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6599AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6599AX\"></sup> for eighty years.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After Ehud came Shamgar son of Anath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6600AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6600AY\"></sup> who struck down six hundred<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6600AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6600AZ\"></sup> Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6600BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6600BA\"></sup> with an oxgoad. He too saved Israel."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Again the Israelites did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6601A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6601A\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6601B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6601B\"></sup> now that Ehud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6601C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6601C\"></sup> was dead.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sold them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6602D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6602D\"></sup> into the hands of Jabin king of Canaan, who reigned in Hazor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6602E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6602E\"></sup> Sisera,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6602F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6602F\"></sup> the commander of his army, was based in Harosheth Haggoyim.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Because he had nine hundred chariots fitted with iron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6603G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6603G\"></sup> and had cruelly oppressed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6603H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6603H\"></sup> the Israelites for twenty years, they cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for help.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now Deborah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6604I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6604I\"></sup> a prophet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6604J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6604J\"></sup> the wife of Lappidoth, was leading Israel at that time.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>She held court<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6605K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6605K\"></sup> under the Palm of Deborah between Ramah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6605L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6605L\"></sup> and Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6605M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6605M\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim, and the Israelites went up to her to have their disputes decided.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>She sent for Barak son of Abinoam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6606N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6606N\"></sup> from Kedesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6606O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6606O\"></sup> in Naphtali and said to him, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, commands you: ‘Go, take with you ten thousand men of Naphtali<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6606P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6606P\"></sup> and Zebulun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6606Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6606Q\"></sup> and lead them up to Mount Tabor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6606R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6606R\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will lead Sisera, the commander of Jabin’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6607S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6607S\"></sup> army, with his chariots and his troops to the Kishon River<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6607T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6607T\"></sup> and give him into your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6607U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6607U\"></sup>’”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Barak said to her, “If you go with me, I will go; but if you don’t go with me, I won’t go.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Certainly I will go with you,” said Deborah. “But because of the course you are taking, the honor will not be yours, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will deliver Sisera into the hands of a woman.” So Deborah went with Barak to Kedesh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6609V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6609V\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>There Barak summoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6610W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6610W\"></sup> Zebulun and Naphtali, and ten thousand men went up under his command. Deborah also went up with him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now Heber the Kenite had left the other Kenites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6611X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6611X\"></sup> the descendants of Hobab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6611Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6611Y\"></sup> Moses’ brother-in-law, and pitched his tent by the great tree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6611Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6611Z\"></sup> in Zaanannim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6611AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6611AA\"></sup> near Kedesh.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When they told Sisera that Barak son of Abinoam had gone up to Mount Tabor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6612AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6612AB\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Sisera summoned from Harosheth Haggoyim to the Kishon River<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6613AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6613AC\"></sup> all his men and his nine hundred chariots fitted with iron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6613AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6613AD\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Deborah said to Barak, “Go! This is the day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given Sisera into your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6614AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6614AE\"></sup> Has not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gone ahead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6614AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6614AF\"></sup> of you?” So Barak went down Mount Tabor, with ten thousand men following him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>At Barak’s advance, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> routed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6615AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6615AG\"></sup> Sisera and all his chariots and army by the sword, and Sisera got down from his chariot and fled on foot.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Barak pursued the chariots and army as far as Harosheth Haggoyim, and all Sisera’s troops fell by the sword; not a man was left.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6616AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6616AH\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Sisera, meanwhile, fled on foot to the tent of Jael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6617AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6617AI\"></sup> the wife of Heber the Kenite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6617AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6617AJ\"></sup> because there was an alliance between Jabin king of Hazor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6617AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6617AK\"></sup> and the family of Heber the Kenite.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Jael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6618AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6618AL\"></sup> went out to meet Sisera and said to him, “Come, my lord, come right in. Don’t be afraid.” So he entered her tent, and she covered him with a blanket.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“I’m thirsty,” he said. “Please give me some water.” She opened a skin of milk,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6619AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6619AM\"></sup> gave him a drink, and covered him up.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Stand in the doorway of the tent,” he told her. “If someone comes by and asks you, ‘Is anyone in there?’ say ‘No.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Jael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6621AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6621AN\"></sup> Heber’s wife, picked up a tent peg and a hammer and went quietly to him while he lay fast asleep,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6621AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6621AO\"></sup> exhausted. She drove the peg through his temple into the ground, and he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6621AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6621AP\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Just then Barak came by in pursuit of Sisera, and Jael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6622AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6622AQ\"></sup> went out to meet him. “Come,” she said, “I will show you the man you’re looking for.” So he went in with her, and there lay Sisera with the tent peg through his temple—dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6622AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6622AR\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>On that day God subdued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6623AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6623AS\"></sup> Jabin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6623AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6623AT\"></sup> king of Canaan before the Israelites.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the hand of the Israelites pressed harder and harder against Jabin king of Canaan until they destroyed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6624AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6624AU\"></sup>"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>On that day Deborah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6625A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6625A\"></sup> and Barak son of Abinoam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6625B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6625B\"></sup> sang this song:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6625C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6625C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“When the princes in Israel take the lead,when the people willingly offer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6626D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6626D\"></sup> themselves—praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6626E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6626E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Hear this, you kings! Listen, you rulers!I, even I, will sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6627F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6627F\"></sup>I will praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, in song.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6627G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6627G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“When you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, went out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6628H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6628H\"></sup> from Seir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6628I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6628I\"></sup>when you marched from the land of Edom,the earth shook,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6628J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6628J\"></sup> the heavens poured,the clouds poured down water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6628K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6628K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The mountains quaked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6629L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6629L\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the One of Sinai,before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“In the days of Shamgar son of Anath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6630M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6630M\"></sup>in the days of Jael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6630N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6630N\"></sup> the highways<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6630O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6630O\"></sup> were abandoned;travelers took to winding paths.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6630P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6630P\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Villagers in Israel would not fight;they held back until I, Deborah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6631Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6631Q\"></sup> arose,until I arose, a mother in Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>God chose new leaders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6632R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6632R\"></sup>when war came to the city gates,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6632S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6632S\"></sup>but not a shield or spear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6632T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6632T\"></sup> was seenamong forty thousand in Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My heart is with Israel’s princes,with the willing volunteers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6633U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6633U\"></sup> among the people.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“You who ride on white donkeys,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6634V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6634V\"></sup>sitting on your saddle blankets,and you who walk along the road,consider",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum mid-line\">11 </sup>the voice of the singers at the watering places.They recite the victories<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6635W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6635W\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,the victories of his villagers in Israel.“Then the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>went down to the city gates.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6635X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6635X\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>‘Wake up,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6636Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6636Y\"></sup> wake up, Deborah!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6636Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6636Z\"></sup>Wake up, wake up, break out in song!Arise, Barak!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6636AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6636AA\"></sup>Take captive your captives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6636AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6636AB\"></sup> son of Abinoam.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“The remnant of the nobles came down;the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came down to me against the mighty.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Some came from Ephraim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6638AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6638AC\"></sup> whose roots were in Amalek;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6638AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6638AD\"></sup>Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6638AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6638AE\"></sup> was with the people who followed you.From Makir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6638AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6638AF\"></sup> captains came down,from Zebulun those who bear a commander’s staff.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The princes of Issachar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6639AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6639AG\"></sup> were with Deborah;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6639AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6639AH\"></sup>yes, Issachar was with Barak,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6639AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6639AI\"></sup>sent under his command into the valley.In the districts of Reubenthere was much searching of heart.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Why did you stay among the sheep pens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6640AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6640AJ\"></sup>to hear the whistling for the flocks?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6640AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6640AK\"></sup>In the districts of Reubenthere was much searching of heart.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6641AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6641AL\"></sup> stayed beyond the Jordan.And Dan, why did he linger by the ships?Asher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6641AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6641AM\"></sup> remained on the coast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6641AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6641AN\"></sup>and stayed in his coves.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The people of Zebulun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6642AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6642AO\"></sup> risked their very lives;so did Naphtali<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6642AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6642AP\"></sup> on the terraced fields.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6642AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6642AQ\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Kings came<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6643AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6643AR\"></sup>, they fought,the kings of Canaan fought.At Taanach, by the waters of Megiddo,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6643AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6643AS\"></sup>they took no plunder of silver.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6643AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6643AT\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>From the heavens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6644AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6644AU\"></sup> the stars fought,from their courses they fought against Sisera.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The river Kishon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6645AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6645AV\"></sup> swept them away,the age-old river, the river Kishon.March on, my soul; be strong!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6645AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6645AW\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then thundered the horses’ hooves—galloping, galloping go his mighty steeds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6646AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6646AX\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>‘Curse Meroz,’ said the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.‘Curse its people bitterly,because they did not come to help the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,to help the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against the mighty.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Most blessed of women<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6648AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6648AY\"></sup> be Jael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6648AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6648AZ\"></sup>the wife of Heber the Kenite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6648BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6648BA\"></sup>most blessed of tent-dwelling women.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He asked for water, and she gave him milk;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6649BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6649BB\"></sup>in a bowl fit for nobles she brought him curdled milk.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Her hand reached for the tent peg,her right hand for the workman’s hammer.She struck Sisera, she crushed his head,she shattered and pierced his temple.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6650BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6650BC\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>At her feet he sank,he fell; there he lay.At her feet he sank, he fell;where he sank, there he fell—dead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6651BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6651BD\"></sup>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Through the window<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6652BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6652BE\"></sup> peered Sisera’s mother;behind the lattice she cried out,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6652BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6652BF\"></sup>‘Why is his chariot so long in coming?Why is the clatter of his chariots delayed?’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The wisest of her ladies answer her;indeed, she keeps saying to herself,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>‘Are they not finding and dividing the spoils:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6654BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6654BG\"></sup>a woman or two for each man,colorful garments as plunder for Sisera,colorful garments embroidered,highly embroidered garments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6654BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6654BH\"></sup> for my neck—all this as plunder?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6654BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6654BI\"></sup>’",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“So may all your enemies perish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6655BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6655BJ\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!But may all who love you be like the sun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6655BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6655BK\"></sup>when it rises in its strength.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6655BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6655BL\"></sup>Then the land had peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6655BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6655BM\"></sup> forty years."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>The Israelites did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6656A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6656A\"></sup> and for seven years he gave them into the hands of the Midianites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6656B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6656B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Because the power of Midian was so oppressive,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6657C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6657C\"></sup> the Israelites prepared shelters for themselves in mountain clefts, caves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6657D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6657D\"></sup> and strongholds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6657E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6657E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Whenever the Israelites planted their crops, the Midianites, Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6658F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6658F\"></sup> and other eastern peoples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6658G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6658G\"></sup> invaded the country.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They camped on the land and ruined the crops<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6659H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6659H\"></sup> all the way to Gaza<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6659I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6659I\"></sup> and did not spare a living thing for Israel, neither sheep nor cattle nor donkeys.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They came up with their livestock and their tents like swarms of locusts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6660J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6660J\"></sup> It was impossible to count them or their camels;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6660K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6660K\"></sup> they invaded the land to ravage it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Midian so impoverished the Israelites that they cried out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6661L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6661L\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for help.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the Israelites cried out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6662M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6662M\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because of Midian,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>he sent them a prophet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6663N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6663N\"></sup> who said, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: I brought you up out of Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6663O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6663O\"></sup> out of the land of slavery.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6663P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6663P\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I rescued you from the hand of the Egyptians. And I delivered you from the hand of all your oppressors;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6664Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6664Q\"></sup> I drove them out before you and gave you their land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6664R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6664R\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I said to you, ‘I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; do not worship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6665S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6665S\"></sup> the gods of the Amorites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6665T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6665T\"></sup> in whose land you live.’ But you have not listened to me.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6666U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6666U\"></sup> came and sat down under the oak in Ophrah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6666V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6666V\"></sup> that belonged to Joash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6666W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6666W\"></sup> the Abiezrite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6666X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6666X\"></sup> where his son Gideon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6666Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6666Y\"></sup> was threshing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6666Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6666Z\"></sup> wheat in a winepress<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6666AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6666AA\"></sup> to keep it from the Midianites.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Gideon, he said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6667AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6667AB\"></sup> mighty warrior.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6667AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6667AC\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Pardon me, my lord,” Gideon replied, “but if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with us, why has all this happened to us? Where are all his wonders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6668AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6668AD\"></sup> that our ancestors told<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6668AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6668AE\"></sup> us about when they said, ‘Did not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bring us up out of Egypt?’ But now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has abandoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6668AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6668AF\"></sup> us and given us into the hand of Midian.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turned to him and said, “Go in the strength you have<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6669AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6669AG\"></sup> and save<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6669AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6669AH\"></sup> Israel out of Midian’s hand. Am I not sending you?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Pardon me, my lord,” Gideon replied, “but how can I save Israel? My clan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6670AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6670AI\"></sup> is the weakest in Manasseh, and I am the least in my family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6670AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6670AJ\"></sup>”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered, “I will be with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6671AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6671AK\"></sup>, and you will strike down all the Midianites, leaving none alive.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Gideon replied, “If now I have found favor in your eyes, give me a sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6672AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6672AL\"></sup> that it is really you talking to me.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Please do not go away until I come back and bring my offering and set it before you.”And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I will wait until you return.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Gideon went inside, prepared a young goat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6674AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6674AM\"></sup> and from an ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6674AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6674AN\"></sup> of flour he made bread without yeast. Putting the meat in a basket and its broth in a pot, he brought them out and offered them to him under the oak.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6674AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6674AO\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The angel of God said to him, “Take the meat and the unleavened bread, place them on this rock,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6675AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6675AP\"></sup> and pour out the broth.” And Gideon did so.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> touched the meat and the unleavened bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6676AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6676AQ\"></sup> with the tip of the staff<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6676AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6676AR\"></sup> that was in his hand. Fire flared from the rock, consuming the meat and the bread. And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> disappeared.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When Gideon realized<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6677AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6677AS\"></sup> that it was the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he exclaimed, “Alas, Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! I have seen the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> face to face!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6677AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6677AT\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Peace! Do not be afraid.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6678AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6678AU\"></sup> You are not going to die.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6678AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6678AV\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Gideon built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there and called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6679AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6679AW\"></sup> it The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Is Peace. To this day it stands in Ophrah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6679AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6679AX\"></sup> of the Abiezrites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>That same night the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Take the second bull from your father’s herd, the one seven years old. Tear down your father’s altar to Baal and cut down the Asherah pole<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6680AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6680AY\"></sup> beside it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then build a proper kind of altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God on the top of this height. Using the wood of the Asherah pole that you cut down, offer the second bull as a burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6681AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6681AZ\"></sup>”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So Gideon took ten of his servants and did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> told him. But because he was afraid of his family and the townspeople, he did it at night rather than in the daytime.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>In the morning when the people of the town got up, there was Baal’s altar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6683BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6683BA\"></sup> demolished, with the Asherah pole beside it cut down and the second bull sacrificed on the newly built altar!",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They asked each other, “Who did this?”When they carefully investigated, they were told, “Gideon son of Joash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6684BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6684BB\"></sup> did it.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The people of the town demanded of Joash, “Bring out your son. He must die, because he has broken down Baal’s altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6685BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6685BC\"></sup> and cut down the Asherah pole beside it.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But Joash replied to the hostile crowd around him, “Are you going to plead Baal’s cause?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6686BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6686BD\"></sup> Are you trying to save him? Whoever fights for him shall be put to death by morning! If Baal really is a god, he can defend himself when someone breaks down his altar.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So because Gideon broke down Baal’s altar, they gave him the name Jerub-Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6687BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6687BE\"></sup> that day, saying, “Let Baal contend with him.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now all the Midianites, Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6688BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6688BF\"></sup> and other eastern peoples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6688BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6688BG\"></sup> joined forces and crossed over the Jordan and camped in the Valley of Jezreel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6688BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6688BH\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came on<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6689BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6689BI\"></sup> Gideon, and he blew a trumpet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6689BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6689BJ\"></sup> summoning the Abiezrites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6689BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6689BK\"></sup> to follow him.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>He sent messengers throughout Manasseh, calling them to arms, and also into Asher,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6690BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6690BL\"></sup> Zebulun and Naphtali,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6690BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6690BM\"></sup> so that they too went up to meet them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6690BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6690BN\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Gideon said to God, “If you will save<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6691BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6691BO\"></sup> Israel by my hand as you have promised—",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>look, I will place a wool fleece<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6692BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6692BP\"></sup> on the threshing floor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6692BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6692BQ\"></sup> If there is dew only on the fleece and all the ground is dry, then I will know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6692BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6692BR\"></sup> that you will save Israel by my hand, as you said.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And that is what happened. Gideon rose early the next day; he squeezed the fleece and wrung out the dew—a bowlful of water.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then Gideon said to God, “Do not be angry with me. Let me make just one more request.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6694BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6694BS\"></sup> Allow me one more test with the fleece, but this time make the fleece dry and let the ground be covered with dew.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>That night God did so. Only the fleece was dry; all the ground was covered with dew.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6695BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6695BT\"></sup>"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Early in the morning, Jerub-Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6696A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6696A\"></sup> (that is, Gideon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6696B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6696B\"></sup>) and all his men camped at the spring of Harod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6696C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6696C\"></sup> The camp of Midian<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6696D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6696D\"></sup> was north of them in the valley near the hill of Moreh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6696E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6696E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gideon, “You have too many men. I cannot deliver Midian into their hands, or Israel would boast against me, ‘My own strength<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6697F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6697F\"></sup> has saved me.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now announce to the army, ‘Anyone who trembles with fear may turn back and leave Mount Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6698G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6698G\"></sup>’” So twenty-two thousand men left, while ten thousand remained.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gideon, “There are still too many<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6699H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6699H\"></sup> men. Take them down to the water, and I will thin them out for you there. If I say, ‘This one shall go with you,’ he shall go; but if I say, ‘This one shall not go with you,’ he shall not go.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So Gideon took the men down to the water. There the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> told him, “Separate those who lap the water with their tongues as a dog laps from those who kneel down to drink.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Three hundred of them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6701I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6701I\"></sup> drank from cupped hands, lapping like dogs. All the rest got down on their knees to drink.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gideon, “With the three hundred men that lapped I will save you and give the Midianites into your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6702J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6702J\"></sup> Let all the others go home.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6702K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6702K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Gideon sent the rest of the Israelites home but kept the three hundred, who took over the provisions and trumpets of the others.Now the camp of Midian lay below him in the valley.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>During that night the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gideon, “Get up, go down against the camp, because I am going to give it into your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6704L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6704L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If you are afraid to attack, go down to the camp with your servant Purah",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and listen to what they are saying. Afterward, you will be encouraged to attack the camp.” So he and Purah his servant went down to the outposts of the camp.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The Midianites, the Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6707M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6707M\"></sup> and all the other eastern peoples had settled in the valley, thick as locusts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6707N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6707N\"></sup> Their camels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6707O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6707O\"></sup> could no more be counted than the sand on the seashore.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6707P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6707P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Gideon arrived just as a man was telling a friend his dream. “I had a dream,” he was saying. “A round loaf of barley bread came tumbling into the Midianite camp. It struck the tent with such force that the tent overturned and collapsed.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>His friend responded, “This can be nothing other than the sword of Gideon son of Joash,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6709Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6709Q\"></sup> the Israelite. God has given the Midianites and the whole camp into his hands.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Gideon heard the dream and its interpretation, he bowed down and worshiped.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6710R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6710R\"></sup> He returned to the camp of Israel and called out, “Get up! The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given the Midianite camp into your hands.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6710S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6710S\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Dividing the three hundred men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6711T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6711T\"></sup> into three companies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6711U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6711U\"></sup> he placed trumpets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6711V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6711V\"></sup> and empty jars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6711W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6711W\"></sup> in the hands of all of them, with torches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6711X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6711X\"></sup> inside.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Watch me,” he told them. “Follow my lead. When I get to the edge of the camp, do exactly as I do.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When I and all who are with me blow our trumpets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6713Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6713Y\"></sup> then from all around the camp blow yours and shout, ‘For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for Gideon.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Gideon and the hundred men with him reached the edge of the camp at the beginning of the middle watch, just after they had changed the guard. They blew their trumpets and broke the jars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6714Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6714Z\"></sup> that were in their hands.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The three companies blew the trumpets and smashed the jars. Grasping the torches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6715AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6715AA\"></sup> in their left hands and holding in their right hands the trumpets they were to blow, they shouted, “A sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6715AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6715AB\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for Gideon!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>While each man held his position around the camp, all the Midianites ran, crying out as they fled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6716AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6716AC\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When the three hundred trumpets sounded,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6717AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6717AD\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> caused the men throughout the camp to turn on each other<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6717AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6717AE\"></sup> with their swords.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6717AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6717AF\"></sup> The army fled to Beth Shittah toward Zererah as far as the border of Abel Meholah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6717AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6717AG\"></sup> near Tabbath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Israelites from Naphtali, Asher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6718AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6718AH\"></sup> and all Manasseh were called out,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6718AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6718AI\"></sup> and they pursued the Midianites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6718AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6718AJ\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Gideon sent messengers throughout the hill country of Ephraim, saying, “Come down against the Midianites and seize the waters of the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6719AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6719AK\"></sup> ahead of them as far as Beth Barah.”So all the men of Ephraim were called out and they seized the waters of the Jordan as far as Beth Barah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They also captured two of the Midianite leaders, Oreb and Zeeb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6720AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6720AL\"></sup>. They killed Oreb at the rock of Oreb,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6720AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6720AM\"></sup> and Zeeb at the winepress of Zeeb. They pursued the Midianites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6720AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6720AN\"></sup> and brought the heads of Oreb and Zeeb to Gideon, who was by the Jordan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6720AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6720AO\"></sup>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Now the Ephraimites asked Gideon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6721A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6721A\"></sup> “Why have you treated us like this? Why didn’t you call us when you went to fight Midian?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6721B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6721B\"></sup>”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6721C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6721C\"></sup> And they challenged him vigorously.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6721D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6721D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But he answered them, “What have I accomplished compared to you? Aren’t the gleanings of Ephraim’s grapes better than the full grape harvest of Abiezer?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6722E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6722E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>God gave Oreb and Zeeb,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6723F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6723F\"></sup> the Midianite leaders, into your hands. What was I able to do compared to you?” At this, their resentment against him subsided.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Gideon and his three hundred men, exhausted yet keeping up the pursuit, came to the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6724G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6724G\"></sup> and crossed it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to the men of Sukkoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6725H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6725H\"></sup> “Give my troops some bread; they are worn out,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6725I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6725I\"></sup> and I am still pursuing Zebah and Zalmunna,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6725J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6725J\"></sup> the kings of Midian.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But the officials of Sukkoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6726K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6726K\"></sup> said, “Do you already have the hands of Zebah and Zalmunna in your possession? Why should we give bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6726L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6726L\"></sup> to your troops?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6726M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6726M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Gideon replied, “Just for that, when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given Zebah and Zalmunna<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6727N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6727N\"></sup> into my hand, I will tear your flesh with desert thorns and briers.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From there he went up to Peniel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6728O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6728O\"></sup> and made the same request of them, but they answered as the men of Sukkoth had.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So he said to the men of Peniel, “When I return in triumph, I will tear down this tower.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6729P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6729P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Zebah and Zalmunna were in Karkor with a force of about fifteen thousand men, all that were left of the armies of the eastern peoples; a hundred and twenty thousand swordsmen had fallen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6730Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6730Q\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Gideon went up by the route of the nomads east of Nobah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6731R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6731R\"></sup> and Jogbehah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6731S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6731S\"></sup> and attacked the unsuspecting army.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Zebah and Zalmunna, the two kings of Midian, fled, but he pursued them and captured them, routing their entire army.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Gideon son of Joash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6733T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6733T\"></sup> then returned from the battle by the Pass of Heres.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6733U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6733U\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He caught a young man of Sukkoth and questioned him, and the young man wrote down for him the names of the seventy-seven officials of Sukkoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6734V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6734V\"></sup> the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6734W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6734W\"></sup> of the town.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Gideon came and said to the men of Sukkoth, “Here are Zebah and Zalmunna, about whom you taunted me by saying, ‘Do you already have the hands of Zebah and Zalmunna in your possession? Why should we give bread to your exhausted men?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6735X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6735X\"></sup>’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He took the elders of the town and taught the men of Sukkoth a lesson<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6736Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6736Y\"></sup> by punishing them with desert thorns and briers.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He also pulled down the tower of Peniel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6737Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6737Z\"></sup> and killed the men of the town.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6737AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6737AA\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he asked Zebah and Zalmunna, “What kind of men did you kill at Tabor?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6738AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6738AB\"></sup>”“Men like you,” they answered, “each one with the bearing of a prince.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Gideon replied, “Those were my brothers, the sons of my own mother. As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6739AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6739AC\"></sup> if you had spared their lives, I would not kill you.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Turning to Jether, his oldest son, he said, “Kill them!” But Jether did not draw his sword, because he was only a boy and was afraid.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Zebah and Zalmunna said, “Come, do it yourself. ‘As is the man, so is his strength.’” So Gideon stepped forward and killed them, and took the ornaments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6741AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6741AD\"></sup> off their camels’ necks.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The Israelites said to Gideon, “Rule over us—you, your son and your grandson—because you have saved us from the hand of Midian.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But Gideon told them, “I will not rule over you, nor will my son rule over you. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will rule<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6743AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6743AE\"></sup> over you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he said, “I do have one request, that each of you give me an earring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6744AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6744AF\"></sup> from your share of the plunder.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6744AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6744AG\"></sup>” (It was the custom of the Ishmaelites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6744AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6744AH\"></sup> to wear gold earrings.)",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They answered, “We’ll be glad to give them.” So they spread out a garment, and each of them threw a ring from his plunder onto it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The weight of the gold rings he asked for came to seventeen hundred shekels, not counting the ornaments, the pendants and the purple garments worn by the kings of Midian or the chains<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6746AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6746AI\"></sup> that were on their camels’ necks.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Gideon made the gold into an ephod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6747AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6747AJ\"></sup> which he placed in Ophrah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6747AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6747AK\"></sup> his town. All Israel prostituted themselves by worshiping it there, and it became a snare<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6747AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6747AL\"></sup> to Gideon and his family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6747AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6747AM\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Thus Midian was subdued before the Israelites and did not raise its head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6748AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6748AN\"></sup> again. During Gideon’s lifetime, the land had peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6748AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6748AO\"></sup> forty years.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jerub-Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6749AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6749AP\"></sup> son of Joash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6749AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6749AQ\"></sup> went back home to live.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He had seventy sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6750AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6750AR\"></sup> of his own, for he had many wives.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>His concubine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6751AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6751AS\"></sup> who lived in Shechem, also bore him a son, whom he named Abimelek.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6751AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6751AT\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Gideon son of Joash died at a good old age<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6752AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6752AU\"></sup> and was buried in the tomb of his father Joash in Ophrah of the Abiezrites.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>No sooner had Gideon died than the Israelites again prostituted themselves to the Baals.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6753AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6753AV\"></sup> They set up Baal-Berith<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6753AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6753AW\"></sup> as their god<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6753AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6753AX\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and did not remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6754AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6754AY\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, who had rescued them from the hands of all their enemies on every side.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They also failed to show any loyalty to the family of Jerub-Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6755AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6755AZ\"></sup> (that is, Gideon) in spite of all the good things he had done for them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6755BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6755BA\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Abimelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6756A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6756A\"></sup> son of Jerub-Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6756B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6756B\"></sup> went to his mother’s brothers in Shechem and said to them and to all his mother’s clan,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Ask all the citizens of Shechem, ‘Which is better for you: to have all seventy of Jerub-Baal’s sons rule over you, or just one man?’ Remember, I am your flesh and blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6757C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6757C\"></sup>”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the brothers repeated all this to the citizens of Shechem, they were inclined to follow Abimelek, for they said, “He is related to us.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They gave him seventy shekels of silver from the temple of Baal-Berith,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6759D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6759D\"></sup> and Abimelek used it to hire reckless scoundrels,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6759E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6759E\"></sup> who became his followers.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He went to his father’s home in Ophrah and on one stone murdered his seventy brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6760F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6760F\"></sup> the sons of Jerub-Baal. But Jotham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6760G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6760G\"></sup> the youngest son of Jerub-Baal, escaped by hiding.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6760H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6760H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then all the citizens of Shechem and Beth Millo<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6761I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6761I\"></sup> gathered beside the great tree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6761J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6761J\"></sup> at the pillar in Shechem to crown Abimelek king.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6762K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6762K\"></sup> was told about this, he climbed up on the top of Mount Gerizim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6762L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6762L\"></sup> and shouted to them, “Listen to me, citizens of Shechem, so that God may listen to you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>One day the trees went out to anoint a king for themselves. They said to the olive tree, ‘Be our king.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“But the olive tree answered, ‘Should I give up my oil, by which both gods and humans are honored, to hold sway over the trees?’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Next, the trees said to the fig tree, ‘Come and be our king.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“But the fig tree replied, ‘Should I give up my fruit, so good and sweet, to hold sway over the trees?’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Then the trees said to the vine, ‘Come and be our king.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“But the vine answered, ‘Should I give up my wine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6768M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6768M\"></sup> which cheers both gods and humans, to hold sway over the trees?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Finally all the trees said to the thornbush, ‘Come and be our king.’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“The thornbush said to the trees, ‘If you really want to anoint me king over you, come and take refuge in my shade;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6770N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6770N\"></sup> but if not, then let fire come out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6770O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6770O\"></sup> of the thornbush and consume the cedars of Lebanon!’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6770P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6770P\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Have you acted honorably and in good faith by making Abimelek king? Have you been fair to Jerub-Baal and his family? Have you treated him as he deserves?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Remember that my father fought for you and risked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6772Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6772Q\"></sup> his life to rescue you from the hand of Midian.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But today you have revolted against my father’s family. You have murdered his seventy sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6773R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6773R\"></sup> on a single stone and have made Abimelek, the son of his female slave, king over the citizens of Shechem because he is related to you.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So have you acted honorably and in good faith toward Jerub-Baal and his family today?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6774S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6774S\"></sup> If you have, may Abimelek be your joy, and may you be his, too!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if you have not, let fire come out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6775T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6775T\"></sup> from Abimelek and consume you, the citizens of Shechem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6775U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6775U\"></sup> and Beth Millo,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6775V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6775V\"></sup> and let fire come out from you, the citizens of Shechem and Beth Millo, and consume Abimelek!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6776W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6776W\"></sup> fled, escaping to Beer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6776X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6776X\"></sup> and he lived there because he was afraid of his brother Abimelek.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>After Abimelek had governed Israel three years,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>God stirred up animosity<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6778Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6778Y\"></sup> between Abimelek and the citizens of Shechem so that they acted treacherously against Abimelek.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>God did this in order that the crime against Jerub-Baal’s seventy sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6779Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6779Z\"></sup> the shedding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6779AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6779AA\"></sup> of their blood, might be avenged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6779AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6779AB\"></sup> on their brother Abimelek and on the citizens of Shechem, who had helped him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6779AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6779AC\"></sup> murder his brothers.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In opposition to him these citizens of Shechem set men on the hilltops to ambush and rob everyone who passed by, and this was reported to Abimelek.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now Gaal son of Ebed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6781AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6781AD\"></sup> moved with his clan into Shechem, and its citizens put their confidence in him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>After they had gone out into the fields and gathered the grapes and trodden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6782AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6782AE\"></sup> them, they held a festival in the temple of their god.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6782AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6782AF\"></sup> While they were eating and drinking, they cursed Abimelek.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Gaal son of Ebed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6783AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6783AG\"></sup> said, “Who<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6783AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6783AH\"></sup> is Abimelek, and why should we Shechemites be subject to him? Isn’t he Jerub-Baal’s son, and isn’t Zebul his deputy? Serve the family of Hamor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6783AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6783AI\"></sup> Shechem’s father! Why should we serve Abimelek?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>If only this people were under my command!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6784AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6784AJ\"></sup> Then I would get rid of him. I would say to Abimelek, ‘Call out your whole army!’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6784AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6784AK\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When Zebul the governor of the city heard what Gaal son of Ebed said, he was very angry.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Under cover he sent messengers to Abimelek, saying, “Gaal son of Ebed and his clan have come to Shechem and are stirring up the city against you.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now then, during the night you and your men should come and lie in wait<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6787AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6787AL\"></sup> in the fields.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the morning at sunrise, advance against the city. When Gaal and his men come out against you, seize the opportunity to attack them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6788AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6788AM\"></sup>”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So Abimelek and all his troops set out by night and took up concealed positions near Shechem in four companies.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Now Gaal son of Ebed had gone out and was standing at the entrance of the city gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6790AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6790AN\"></sup> just as Abimelek and his troops came out from their hiding place.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6790AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6790AO\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When Gaal saw them, he said to Zebul, “Look, people are coming down from the tops of the mountains!”Zebul replied, “You mistake the shadows of the mountains for men.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But Gaal spoke up again: “Look, people are coming down from the central hill, and a company is coming from the direction of the diviners’ tree.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Zebul said to him, “Where is your big talk now, you who said, ‘Who is Abimelek that we should be subject to him?’ Aren’t these the men you ridiculed?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6793AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6793AP\"></sup> Go out and fight them!”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>So Gaal led out the citizens of Shechem and fought Abimelek.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Abimelek chased him all the way to the entrance of the gate, and many were killed as they fled.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then Abimelek stayed in Arumah, and Zebul drove Gaal and his clan out of Shechem.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The next day the people of Shechem went out to the fields, and this was reported to Abimelek.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>So he took his men, divided them into three companies<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6798AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6798AQ\"></sup> and set an ambush<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6798AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6798AR\"></sup> in the fields. When he saw the people coming out of the city, he rose to attack them.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Abimelek and the companies with him rushed forward to a position at the entrance of the city gate. Then two companies attacked those in the fields and struck them down.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>All that day Abimelek pressed his attack against the city until he had captured it and killed its people. Then he destroyed the city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6800AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6800AS\"></sup> and scattered salt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6800AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6800AT\"></sup> over it.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>On hearing this, the citizens in the tower of Shechem went into the stronghold of the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6801AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6801AU\"></sup> of El-Berith.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When Abimelek heard that they had assembled there,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>he and all his men went up Mount Zalmon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6803AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6803AV\"></sup> He took an ax and cut off some branches, which he lifted to his shoulders. He ordered the men with him, “Quick! Do what you have seen me do!”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>So all the men cut branches and followed Abimelek. They piled them against the stronghold and set it on fire with the people still inside. So all the people in the tower of Shechem, about a thousand men and women, also died.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Next Abimelek went to Thebez<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6805AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6805AW\"></sup> and besieged it and captured it.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Inside the city, however, was a strong tower, to which all the men and women—all the people of the city—had fled. They had locked themselves in and climbed up on the tower roof.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Abimelek went to the tower and attacked it. But as he approached the entrance to the tower to set it on fire,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>a woman dropped an upper millstone on his head and cracked his skull.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6808AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6808AX\"></sup>",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Hurriedly he called to his armor-bearer, “Draw your sword and kill me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6809AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6809AY\"></sup> so that they can’t say, ‘A woman killed him.’” So his servant ran him through, and he died.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>When the Israelites saw that Abimelek was dead, they went home.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Thus God repaid the wickedness that Abimelek had done to his father by murdering his seventy brothers.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>God also made the people of Shechem pay for all their wickedness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6812AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6812AZ\"></sup> The curse of Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6812BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6812BA\"></sup> son of Jerub-Baal came on them."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>After the time of Abimelek,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6813A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6813A\"></sup> a man of Issachar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6813B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6813B\"></sup> named Tola son of Puah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6813C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6813C\"></sup> the son of Dodo, rose to save<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6813D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6813D\"></sup> Israel. He lived in Shamir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6813E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6813E\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He led Israel twenty-three years; then he died, and was buried in Shamir.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He was followed by Jair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6815F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6815F\"></sup> of Gilead, who led Israel twenty-two years.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He had thirty sons, who rode thirty donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6816G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6816G\"></sup> They controlled thirty towns in Gilead, which to this day are called Havvoth Jair.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6816H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6816H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Jair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6817I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6817I\"></sup> died, he was buried in Kamon.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Again the Israelites did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6818J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6818J\"></sup> They served the Baals and the Ashtoreths,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6818K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6818K\"></sup> and the gods of Aram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6818L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6818L\"></sup> the gods of Sidon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6818M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6818M\"></sup> the gods of Moab, the gods of the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6818N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6818N\"></sup> and the gods of the Philistines.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6818O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6818O\"></sup> And because the Israelites forsook the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6818P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6818P\"></sup> and no longer served him,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>he became angry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6819Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6819Q\"></sup> with them. He sold them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6819R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6819R\"></sup> into the hands of the Philistines and the Ammonites,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>who that year shattered and crushed them. For eighteen years they oppressed all the Israelites on the east side of the Jordan in Gilead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6820S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6820S\"></sup> the land of the Amorites.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The Ammonites also crossed the Jordan to fight against Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6821T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6821T\"></sup> Benjamin and Ephraim;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6821U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6821U\"></sup> Israel was in great distress.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the Israelites cried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6822V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6822V\"></sup> out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “We have sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6822W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6822W\"></sup> against you, forsaking our God and serving the Baals.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6822X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6822X\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> replied, “When the Egyptians,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6823Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6823Y\"></sup> the Amorites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6823Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6823Z\"></sup> the Ammonites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6823AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6823AA\"></sup> the Philistines,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6823AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6823AB\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the Sidonians, the Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6824AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6824AC\"></sup> and the Maonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6824AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6824AD\"></sup> oppressed you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6824AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6824AE\"></sup> and you cried to me for help, did I not save you from their hands?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But you have forsaken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6825AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6825AF\"></sup> me and served other gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6825AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6825AG\"></sup> so I will no longer save you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Go and cry out to the gods you have chosen. Let them save<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6826AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6826AH\"></sup> you when you are in trouble!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6826AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6826AI\"></sup>”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the Israelites said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “We have sinned. Do with us whatever you think best,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6827AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6827AJ\"></sup> but please rescue us now.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then they got rid of the foreign gods among them and served the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6828AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6828AK\"></sup> And he could bear Israel’s misery<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6828AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6828AL\"></sup> no longer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6828AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6828AM\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When the Ammonites were called to arms and camped in Gilead, the Israelites assembled and camped at Mizpah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6829AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6829AN\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The leaders of the people of Gilead said to each other, “Whoever will take the lead in attacking the Ammonites will be head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6830AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6830AO\"></sup> over all who live in Gilead.”"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Jephthah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6831A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6831A\"></sup> the Gileadite was a mighty warrior.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6831B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6831B\"></sup> His father was Gilead;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6831C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6831C\"></sup> his mother was a prostitute.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6831D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6831D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Gilead’s wife also bore him sons, and when they were grown up, they drove Jephthah away. “You are not going to get any inheritance in our family,” they said, “because you are the son of another woman.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Jephthah fled from his brothers and settled in the land of Tob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6833E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6833E\"></sup> where a gang of scoundrels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6833F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6833F\"></sup> gathered around him and followed him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Some time later, when the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6834G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6834G\"></sup> were fighting against Israel,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the elders of Gilead went to get Jephthah from the land of Tob.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Come,” they said, “be our commander, so we can fight the Ammonites.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Jephthah said to them, “Didn’t you hate me and drive me from my father’s house?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6837H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6837H\"></sup> Why do you come to me now, when you’re in trouble?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The elders of Gilead said to him, “Nevertheless, we are turning to you now; come with us to fight the Ammonites, and you will be head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6838I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6838I\"></sup> over all of us who live in Gilead.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jephthah answered, “Suppose you take me back to fight the Ammonites and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives them to me—will I really be your head?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The elders of Gilead replied, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is our witness;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6840J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6840J\"></sup> we will certainly do as you say.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Jephthah went with the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6841K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6841K\"></sup> of Gilead, and the people made him head and commander over them. And he repeated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6841L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6841L\"></sup> all his words before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Mizpah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6841M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6841M\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Jephthah sent messengers to the Ammonite king with the question: “What do you have against me that you have attacked my country?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king of the Ammonites answered Jephthah’s messengers, “When Israel came up out of Egypt, they took away my land from the Arnon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6843N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6843N\"></sup> to the Jabbok,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6843O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6843O\"></sup> all the way to the Jordan. Now give it back peaceably.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jephthah sent back messengers to the Ammonite king,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>saying:“This is what Jephthah says: Israel did not take the land of Moab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6845P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6845P\"></sup> or the land of the Ammonites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6845Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6845Q\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But when they came up out of Egypt, Israel went through the wilderness to the Red Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6846R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6846R\"></sup> and on to Kadesh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6846S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6846S\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Israel sent messengers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6847T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6847T\"></sup> to the king of Edom, saying, ‘Give us permission to go through your country,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6847U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6847U\"></sup> but the king of Edom would not listen. They sent also to the king of Moab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6847V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6847V\"></sup> and he refused.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6847W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6847W\"></sup> So Israel stayed at Kadesh.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Next they traveled through the wilderness, skirted the lands of Edom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6848X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6848X\"></sup> and Moab, passed along the eastern side<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6848Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6848Y\"></sup> of the country of Moab, and camped on the other side of the Arnon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6848Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6848Z\"></sup> They did not enter the territory of Moab, for the Arnon was its border.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Then Israel sent messengers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6849AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6849AA\"></sup> to Sihon king of the Amorites, who ruled in Heshbon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6849AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6849AB\"></sup> and said to him, ‘Let us pass through your country to our own place.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6849AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6849AC\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Sihon, however, did not trust Israel to pass through his territory. He mustered all his troops and encamped at Jahaz and fought with Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6850AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6850AD\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, gave Sihon and his whole army into Israel’s hands, and they defeated them. Israel took over all the land of the Amorites who lived in that country,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>capturing all of it from the Arnon to the Jabbok and from the desert to the Jordan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6852AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6852AE\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Now since the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, has driven the Amorites out before his people Israel, what right have you to take it over?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Will you not take what your god Chemosh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6854AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6854AF\"></sup> gives you? Likewise, whatever the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God has given us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6854AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6854AG\"></sup> we will possess.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Are you any better than Balak son of Zippor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6855AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6855AH\"></sup> king of Moab? Did he ever quarrel with Israel or fight with them?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6855AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6855AI\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For three hundred years Israel occupied<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6856AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6856AJ\"></sup> Heshbon, Aroer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6856AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6856AK\"></sup> the surrounding settlements and all the towns along the Arnon. Why didn’t you retake them during that time?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>I have not wronged you, but you are doing me wrong by waging war against me. Let the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the Judge,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6857AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6857AL\"></sup> decide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6857AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6857AM\"></sup> the dispute this day between the Israelites and the Ammonites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6857AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6857AN\"></sup>”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The king of Ammon, however, paid no attention to the message Jephthah sent him.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6859AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6859AO\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came on Jephthah. He crossed Gilead and Manasseh, passed through Mizpah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6859AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6859AP\"></sup> of Gilead, and from there he advanced against the Ammonites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6859AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6859AQ\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Jephthah made a vow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6860AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6860AR\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: “If you give the Ammonites into my hands,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>whatever comes out of the door of my house to meet me when I return in triumph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6861AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6861AS\"></sup> from the Ammonites will be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s, and I will sacrifice it as a burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6861AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6861AT\"></sup>”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then Jephthah went over to fight the Ammonites, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them into his hands.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He devastated twenty towns from Aroer to the vicinity of Minnith,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6863AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6863AU\"></sup> as far as Abel Keramim. Thus Israel subdued Ammon.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Jephthah returned to his home in Mizpah, who should come out to meet him but his daughter, dancing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6864AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6864AV\"></sup> to the sound of timbrels!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6864AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6864AW\"></sup> She was an only child.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6864AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6864AX\"></sup> Except for her he had neither son nor daughter.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>When he saw her, he tore his clothes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6865AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6865AY\"></sup> and cried, “Oh no, my daughter! You have brought me down and I am devastated. I have made a vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that I cannot break.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6865AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6865AZ\"></sup>”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“My father,” she replied, “you have given your word to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Do to me just as you promised,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6866BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6866BA\"></sup> now that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has avenged you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6866BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6866BB\"></sup> of your enemies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6866BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6866BC\"></sup> the Ammonites.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But grant me this one request,” she said. “Give me two months to roam the hills and weep with my friends, because I will never marry.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“You may go,” he said. And he let her go for two months. She and her friends went into the hills and wept because she would never marry.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>After the two months, she returned to her father, and he did to her as he had vowed. And she was a virgin.From this comes the Israelite tradition",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>that each year the young women of Israel go out for four days to commemorate the daughter of Jephthah the Gileadite."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>The Ephraimite forces were called out, and they crossed over to Zaphon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6871A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6871A\"></sup> They said to Jephthah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6871B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6871B\"></sup> “Why did you go to fight the Ammonites without calling us to go with you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6871C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6871C\"></sup> We’re going to burn down your house over your head.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jephthah answered, “I and my people were engaged in a great struggle with the Ammonites, and although I called, you didn’t save me out of their hands.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When I saw that you wouldn’t help, I took my life in my hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6873D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6873D\"></sup> and crossed over to fight the Ammonites, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave me the victory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6873E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6873E\"></sup> over them. Now why have you come up today to fight me?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jephthah then called together the men of Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6874F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6874F\"></sup> and fought against Ephraim. The Gileadites struck them down because the Ephraimites had said, “You Gileadites are renegades from Ephraim and Manasseh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6874G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6874G\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Gileadites captured the fords of the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6875H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6875H\"></sup> leading to Ephraim, and whenever a survivor of Ephraim said, “Let me cross over,” the men of Gilead asked him, “Are you an Ephraimite?” If he replied, “No,”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>they said, “All right, say ‘Shibboleth.’” If he said, “Sibboleth,” because he could not pronounce the word correctly, they seized him and killed him at the fords of the Jordan. Forty-two thousand Ephraimites were killed at that time.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Jephthah led Israel six years. Then Jephthah the Gileadite died and was buried in a town in Gilead.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>After him, Ibzan of Bethlehem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6878I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6878I\"></sup> led Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He had thirty sons and thirty daughters. He gave his daughters away in marriage to those outside his clan, and for his sons he brought in thirty young women as wives from outside his clan. Ibzan led Israel seven years.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Ibzan died and was buried in Bethlehem.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>After him, Elon the Zebulunite led Israel ten years.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Elon died and was buried in Aijalon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6882J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6882J\"></sup> in the land of Zebulun.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>After him, Abdon son of Hillel, from Pirathon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6883K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6883K\"></sup> led Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He had forty sons and thirty grandsons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6884L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6884L\"></sup> who rode on seventy donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6884M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6884M\"></sup> He led Israel eight years.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Abdon son of Hillel died and was buried at Pirathon in Ephraim, in the hill country of the Amalekites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6885N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6885N\"></sup>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Again the Israelites did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered them into the hands of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6886A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6886A\"></sup> for forty years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6886B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6886B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>A certain man of Zorah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6887C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6887C\"></sup> named Manoah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6887D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6887D\"></sup> from the clan of the Danites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6887E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6887E\"></sup> had a wife who was childless,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6887F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6887F\"></sup> unable to give birth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6888G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6888G\"></sup> appeared to her<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6888H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6888H\"></sup> and said, “You are barren and childless, but you are going to become pregnant and give birth to a son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6888I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6888I\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now see to it that you drink no wine or other fermented drink<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6889J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6889J\"></sup> and that you do not eat anything unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6889K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6889K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You will become pregnant and have a son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6890L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6890L\"></sup> whose head is never to be touched by a razor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6890M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6890M\"></sup> because the boy is to be a Nazirite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6890N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6890N\"></sup> dedicated to God from the womb. He will take the lead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6890O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6890O\"></sup> in delivering Israel from the hands of the Philistines.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the woman went to her husband and told him, “A man of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6891P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6891P\"></sup> came to me. He looked like an angel of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6891Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6891Q\"></sup> very awesome.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6891R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6891R\"></sup> I didn’t ask him where he came from, and he didn’t tell me his name.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But he said to me, ‘You will become pregnant and have a son. Now then, drink no wine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6892S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6892S\"></sup> or other fermented drink<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6892T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6892T\"></sup> and do not eat anything unclean, because the boy will be a Nazirite of God from the womb until the day of his death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6892U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6892U\"></sup>’”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Manoah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6893V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6893V\"></sup> prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: “Pardon your servant, Lord. I beg you to let the man of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6893W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6893W\"></sup> you sent to us come again to teach us how to bring up the boy who is to be born.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>God heard Manoah, and the angel of God came again to the woman while she was out in the field; but her husband Manoah was not with her.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The woman hurried to tell her husband, “He’s here! The man who appeared to me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6895X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6895X\"></sup> the other day!”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Manoah got up and followed his wife. When he came to the man, he said, “Are you the man who talked to my wife?”“I am,” he said.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Manoah asked him, “When your words are fulfilled, what is to be the rule that governs the boy’s life and work?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered, “Your wife must do all that I have told her.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>She must not eat anything that comes from the grapevine, nor drink any wine or other fermented drink<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6899Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6899Y\"></sup> nor eat anything unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6899Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6899Z\"></sup> She must do everything I have commanded her.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Manoah said to the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “We would like you to stay until we prepare a young goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6900AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6900AA\"></sup> for you.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> replied, “Even though you detain me, I will not eat any of your food. But if you prepare a burnt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6901AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6901AB\"></sup> offer it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” (Manoah did not realize<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6901AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6901AC\"></sup> that it was the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.)",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Manoah inquired of the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “What is your name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6902AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6902AD\"></sup> so that we may honor you when your word comes true?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He replied, “Why do you ask my name?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6903AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6903AE\"></sup> It is beyond understanding.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Manoah took a young goat, together with the grain offering, and sacrificed it on a rock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6904AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6904AF\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did an amazing thing while Manoah and his wife watched:",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As the flame<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6905AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6905AG\"></sup> blazed up from the altar toward heaven, the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> ascended in the flame. Seeing this, Manoah and his wife fell with their faces to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6905AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6905AH\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not show himself again to Manoah and his wife, Manoah realized<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6906AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6906AI\"></sup> that it was the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“We are doomed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6907AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6907AJ\"></sup> to die!” he said to his wife. “We have seen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6907AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6907AK\"></sup> God!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But his wife answered, “If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had meant to kill us, he would not have accepted a burnt offering and grain offering from our hands, nor shown us all these things or now told us this.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6908AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6908AL\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The woman gave birth to a boy and named him Samson.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6909AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6909AM\"></sup> He grew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6909AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6909AN\"></sup> and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6909AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6909AO\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began to stir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6910AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6910AP\"></sup> him while he was in Mahaneh Dan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6910AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6910AQ\"></sup> between Zorah and Eshtaol."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Samson<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6911A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6911A\"></sup> went down to Timnah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6911B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6911B\"></sup> and saw there a young Philistine woman.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When he returned, he said to his father and mother, “I have seen a Philistine woman in Timnah; now get her for me as my wife.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6912C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6912C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>His father and mother replied, “Isn’t there an acceptable woman among your relatives or among all our people?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6913D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6913D\"></sup> Must you go to the uncircumcised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6913E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6913E\"></sup> Philistines to get a wife?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6913F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6913F\"></sup>”But Samson said to his father, “Get her for me. She’s the right one for me.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>(His parents did not know that this was from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6914G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6914G\"></sup> who was seeking an occasion to confront the Philistines;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6914H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6914H\"></sup> for at that time they were ruling over Israel.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6914I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6914I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Samson went down to Timnah together with his father and mother. As they approached the vineyards of Timnah, suddenly a young lion came roaring toward him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came powerfully upon him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6916J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6916J\"></sup> so that he tore the lion apart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6916K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6916K\"></sup> with his bare hands as he might have torn a young goat. But he told neither his father nor his mother what he had done.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he went down and talked with the woman, and he liked her.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Some time later, when he went back to marry her, he turned aside to look at the lion’s carcass, and in it he saw a swarm of bees and some honey.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He scooped out the honey with his hands and ate as he went along. When he rejoined his parents, he gave them some, and they too ate it. But he did not tell them that he had taken the honey from the lion’s carcass.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now his father went down to see the woman. And there Samson held a feast,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6920L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6920L\"></sup> as was customary for young men.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the people saw him, they chose thirty men to be his companions.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Let me tell you a riddle,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6922M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6922M\"></sup>” Samson said to them. “If you can give me the answer within the seven days of the feast,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6922N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6922N\"></sup> I will give you thirty linen garments and thirty sets of clothes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6922O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6922O\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If you can’t tell me the answer, you must give me thirty linen garments and thirty sets of clothes.”“Tell us your riddle,” they said. “Let’s hear it.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He replied,“Out of the eater, something to eat;out of the strong, something sweet.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6924P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6924P\"></sup>For three days they could not give the answer.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>On the fourth day, they said to Samson’s wife, “Coax<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6925Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6925Q\"></sup> your husband into explaining the riddle for us, or we will burn you and your father’s household to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6925R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6925R\"></sup> Did you invite us here to steal our property?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Samson’s wife threw herself on him, sobbing, “You hate me! You don’t really love me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6926S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6926S\"></sup> You’ve given my people a riddle, but you haven’t told me the answer.”“I haven’t even explained it to my father or mother,” he replied, “so why should I explain it to you?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She cried the whole seven days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6927T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6927T\"></sup> of the feast. So on the seventh day he finally told her, because she continued to press him. She in turn explained the riddle to her people.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Before sunset on the seventh day the men of the town said to him,“What is sweeter than honey?What is stronger than a lion?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6928U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6928U\"></sup>Samson said to them,“If you had not plowed with my heifer,you would not have solved my riddle.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came powerfully upon him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6929V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6929V\"></sup> He went down to Ashkelon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6929W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6929W\"></sup> struck down thirty of their men, stripped them of everything and gave their clothes to those who had explained the riddle. Burning with anger,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6929X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6929X\"></sup> he returned to his father’s home.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Samson’s wife was given to one of his companions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6930Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6930Y\"></sup> who had attended him at the feast."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Later on, at the time of wheat harvest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6931A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6931A\"></sup> Samson<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6931B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6931B\"></sup> took a young goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6931C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6931C\"></sup> and went to visit his wife. He said, “I’m going to my wife’s room.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6931D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6931D\"></sup> But her father would not let him go in.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“I was so sure you hated her,” he said, “that I gave her to your companion.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6932E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6932E\"></sup> Isn’t her younger sister more attractive? Take her instead.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Samson said to them, “This time I have a right to get even with the Philistines; I will really harm them.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he went out and caught three hundred foxes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6934F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6934F\"></sup> and tied them tail to tail in pairs. He then fastened a torch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6934G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6934G\"></sup> to every pair of tails,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>lit the torches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6935H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6935H\"></sup> and let the foxes loose in the standing grain of the Philistines. He burned up the shocks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6935I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6935I\"></sup> and standing grain, together with the vineyards and olive groves.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the Philistines asked, “Who did this?” they were told, “Samson, the Timnite’s son-in-law, because his wife was given to his companion.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6936J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6936J\"></sup>”So the Philistines went up and burned her<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6936K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6936K\"></sup> and her father to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6936L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6936L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Samson said to them, “Since you’ve acted like this, I swear that I won’t stop until I get my revenge on you.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He attacked them viciously and slaughtered many of them. Then he went down and stayed in a cave in the rock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6938M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6938M\"></sup> of Etam.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6938N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6938N\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The Philistines went up and camped in Judah, spreading out near Lehi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6939O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6939O\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The people of Judah asked, “Why have you come to fight us?”“We have come to take Samson prisoner,” they answered, “to do to him as he did to us.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then three thousand men from Judah went down to the cave in the rock of Etam and said to Samson, “Don’t you realize that the Philistines are rulers over us?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6941P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6941P\"></sup> What have you done to us?”He answered, “I merely did to them what they did to me.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They said to him, “We’ve come to tie you up and hand you over to the Philistines.”Samson said, “Swear to me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6942Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6942Q\"></sup> that you won’t kill me yourselves.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Agreed,” they answered. “We will only tie you up and hand you over to them. We will not kill you.” So they bound him with two new ropes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6943R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6943R\"></sup> and led him up from the rock.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>As he approached Lehi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6944S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6944S\"></sup> the Philistines came toward him shouting. The Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came powerfully upon him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6944T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6944T\"></sup> The ropes on his arms became like charred flax,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6944U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6944U\"></sup> and the bindings dropped from his hands.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Finding a fresh jawbone of a donkey, he grabbed it and struck down a thousand men.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6945V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6945V\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Samson said,“With a donkey’s jawboneI have made donkeys of them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6946W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6946W\"></sup>With a donkey’s jawboneI have killed a thousand men.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When he finished speaking, he threw away the jawbone; and the place was called Ramath Lehi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6947X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6947X\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Because he was very thirsty, he cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6948Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6948Y\"></sup> “You have given your servant this great victory.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6948Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6948Z\"></sup> Must I now die of thirst and fall into the hands of the uncircumcised?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then God opened up the hollow place in Lehi, and water came out of it. When Samson drank, his strength returned and he revived.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6949AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6949AA\"></sup> So the spring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6949AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6949AB\"></sup> was called En Hakkore, and it is still there in Lehi.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Samson led Israel for twenty years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6950AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6950AC\"></sup> in the days of the Philistines."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>One day Samson<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6951A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6951A\"></sup> went to Gaza,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6951B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6951B\"></sup> where he saw a prostitute.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6951C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6951C\"></sup> He went in to spend the night with her.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The people of Gaza were told, “Samson is here!” So they surrounded the place and lay in wait for him all night at the city gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6952D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6952D\"></sup> They made no move during the night, saying, “At dawn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6952E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6952E\"></sup> we’ll kill him.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Samson lay there only until the middle of the night. Then he got up and took hold of the doors of the city gate, together with the two posts, and tore them loose, bar and all. He lifted them to his shoulders and carried them to the top of the hill that faces Hebron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6953F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6953F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Some time later, he fell in love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6954G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6954G\"></sup> with a woman in the Valley of Sorek whose name was Delilah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6954H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6954H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The rulers of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6955I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6955I\"></sup> went to her and said, “See if you can lure<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6955J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6955J\"></sup> him into showing you the secret of his great strength<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6955K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6955K\"></sup> and how we can overpower him so we may tie him up and subdue him. Each one of us will give you eleven hundred shekels of silver.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6955L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6955L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Delilah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6956M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6956M\"></sup> said to Samson, “Tell me the secret of your great strength and how you can be tied up and subdued.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Samson answered her, “If anyone ties me with seven fresh bowstrings that have not been dried, I’ll become as weak as any other man.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the rulers of the Philistines brought her seven fresh bowstrings that had not been dried, and she tied him with them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>With men hidden in the room,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6959N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6959N\"></sup> she called to him, “Samson, the Philistines are upon you!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6959O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6959O\"></sup> But he snapped the bowstrings as easily as a piece of string snaps when it comes close to a flame. So the secret of his strength was not discovered.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Delilah said to Samson, “You have made a fool of me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6960P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6960P\"></sup> you lied to me. Come now, tell me how you can be tied.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He said, “If anyone ties me securely with new ropes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6961Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6961Q\"></sup> that have never been used, I’ll become as weak as any other man.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Delilah took new ropes and tied him with them. Then, with men hidden in the room, she called to him, “Samson, the Philistines are upon you!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6962R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6962R\"></sup> But he snapped the ropes off his arms as if they were threads.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Delilah then said to Samson, “All this time you have been making a fool of me and lying to me. Tell me how you can be tied.”He replied, “If you weave the seven braids of my head into the fabric on the loom and tighten it with the pin, I’ll become as weak as any other man.” So while he was sleeping, Delilah took the seven braids of his head, wove them into the fabric",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and tightened it with the pin.Again she called to him, “Samson, the Philistines are upon you!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6964S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6964S\"></sup> He awoke from his sleep and pulled up the pin and the loom, with the fabric.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then she said to him, “How can you say, ‘I love you,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6965T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6965T\"></sup> when you won’t confide in me? This is the third time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6965U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6965U\"></sup> you have made a fool of me and haven’t told me the secret of your great strength.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6965V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6965V\"></sup>”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>With such nagging she prodded him day after day until he was sick to death of it.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he told her everything.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6967W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6967W\"></sup> “No razor has ever been used on my head,” he said, “because I have been a Nazirite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6967X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6967X\"></sup> dedicated to God from my mother’s womb. If my head were shaved, my strength would leave me, and I would become as weak as any other man.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Delilah saw that he had told her everything, she sent word to the rulers of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6968Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6968Y\"></sup>, “Come back once more; he has told me everything.” So the rulers of the Philistines returned with the silver in their hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6968Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6968Z\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After putting him to sleep on her lap, she called for someone to shave off the seven braids of his hair, and so began to subdue him. And his strength left him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6969AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6969AA\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then she called, “Samson, the Philistines are upon you!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6970AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6970AB\"></sup>He awoke from his sleep and thought, “I’ll go out as before and shake myself free.” But he did not know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had left him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6970AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6970AC\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6971AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6971AD\"></sup> seized him, gouged out his eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6971AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6971AE\"></sup> and took him down to Gaza.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6971AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6971AF\"></sup> Binding him with bronze shackles, they set him to grinding grain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6971AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6971AG\"></sup> in the prison.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the hair on his head began to grow again after it had been shaved.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now the rulers of the Philistines assembled to offer a great sacrifice to Dagon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6973AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6973AH\"></sup> their god and to celebrate, saying, “Our god has delivered Samson, our enemy, into our hands.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When the people saw him, they praised their god,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6974AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6974AI\"></sup> saying,“Our god has delivered our enemyinto our hands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6974AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6974AJ\"></sup>the one who laid waste our landand multiplied our slain.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>While they were in high spirits,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6975AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6975AK\"></sup> they shouted, “Bring out Samson to entertain us.” So they called Samson out of the prison, and he performed for them.When they stood him among the pillars,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Samson said to the servant who held his hand, “Put me where I can feel the pillars that support the temple, so that I may lean against them.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now the temple was crowded with men and women; all the rulers of the Philistines were there, and on the roof<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6977AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6977AL\"></sup> were about three thousand men and women watching Samson perform.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Samson prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6978AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6978AM\"></sup> “Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, remember me. Please, God, strengthen me just once more, and let me with one blow get revenge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6978AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6978AN\"></sup> on the Philistines for my two eyes.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Samson reached toward the two central pillars on which the temple stood. Bracing himself against them, his right hand on the one and his left hand on the other,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Samson said, “Let me die with the Philistines!” Then he pushed with all his might, and down came the temple on the rulers and all the people in it. Thus he killed many more when he died than while he lived.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then his brothers and his father’s whole family went down to get him. They brought him back and buried him between Zorah and Eshtaol in the tomb of Manoah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6981AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6981AO\"></sup> his father. He had led<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6981AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6981AP\"></sup> Israel twenty years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6981AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6981AQ\"></sup>"
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Now a man named Micah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6982A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6982A\"></sup> from the hill country of Ephraim",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>said to his mother, “The eleven hundred shekels of silver that were taken from you and about which I heard you utter a curse—I have that silver with me; I took it.”Then his mother said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bless you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6983B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6983B\"></sup> my son!”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When he returned the eleven hundred shekels of silver to his mother, she said, “I solemnly consecrate my silver to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for my son to make an image overlaid with silver.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6984C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6984C\"></sup> I will give it back to you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So after he returned the silver to his mother, she took two hundred shekels of silver and gave them to a silversmith, who used them to make the idol.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6985D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6985D\"></sup> And it was put in Micah’s house.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now this man Micah had a shrine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6986E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6986E\"></sup> and he made an ephod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6986F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6986F\"></sup> and some household gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6986G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6986G\"></sup> and installed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6986H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6986H\"></sup> one of his sons as his priest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6986I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6986I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In those days Israel had no king;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6987J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6987J\"></sup> everyone did as they saw fit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6987K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6987K\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>A young Levite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6988L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6988L\"></sup> from Bethlehem in Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6988M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6988M\"></sup> who had been living within the clan of Judah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>left that town in search of some other place to stay. On his way he came to Micah’s house in the hill country of Ephraim.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Micah asked him, “Where are you from?”“I’m a Levite from Bethlehem in Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6990N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6990N\"></sup>” he said, “and I’m looking for a place to stay.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Micah said to him, “Live with me and be my father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6991O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6991O\"></sup> and priest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6991P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6991P\"></sup> and I’ll give you ten shekels of silver a year, your clothes and your food.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the Levite agreed to live with him, and the young man became like one of his sons to him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Micah installed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6993Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6993Q\"></sup> the Levite, and the young man became his priest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6993R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6993R\"></sup> and lived in his house.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Micah said, “Now I know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be good to me, since this Levite has become my priest.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6994S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6994S\"></sup>"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>In those days Israel had no king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6995A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6995A\"></sup>And in those days the tribe of the Danites was seeking a place of their own where they might settle, because they had not yet come into an inheritance among the tribes of Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6995B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6995B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the Danites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6996C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6996C\"></sup> sent five of their leading men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6996D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6996D\"></sup> from Zorah and Eshtaol to spy out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6996E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6996E\"></sup> the land and explore it. These men represented all the Danites. They told them, “Go, explore the land.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6996F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6996F\"></sup>So they entered the hill country of Ephraim and came to the house of Micah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6996G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6996G\"></sup> where they spent the night.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When they were near Micah’s house, they recognized the voice of the young Levite;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6997H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6997H\"></sup> so they turned in there and asked him, “Who brought you here? What are you doing in this place? Why are you here?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He told them what Micah had done for him, and said, “He has hired me and I am his priest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6998I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6998I\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then they said to him, “Please inquire of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6999J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6999J\"></sup> to learn whether our journey will be successful.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The priest answered them, “Go in peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7000K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7000K\"></sup>. Your journey has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s approval.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So the five men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7001L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7001L\"></sup> left and came to Laish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7001M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7001M\"></sup> where they saw that the people were living in safety, like the Sidonians, at peace and secure.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7001N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7001N\"></sup> And since their land lacked nothing, they were prosperous. Also, they lived a long way from the Sidonians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7001O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7001O\"></sup> and had no relationship with anyone else.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When they returned to Zorah and Eshtaol, their fellow Danites asked them, “How did you find things?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They answered, “Come on, let’s attack them! We have seen the land, and it is very good. Aren’t you going to do something? Don’t hesitate to go there and take it over.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7003P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7003P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When you get there, you will find an unsuspecting people and a spacious land that God has put into your hands, a land that lacks nothing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7004Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7004Q\"></sup> whatever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7004R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7004R\"></sup>”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then six hundred men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7005S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7005S\"></sup> of the Danites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7005T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7005T\"></sup> armed for battle, set out from Zorah and Eshtaol.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>On their way they set up camp near Kiriath Jearim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7006U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7006U\"></sup> in Judah. This is why the place west of Kiriath Jearim is called Mahaneh Dan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7006V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7006V\"></sup> to this day.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>From there they went on to the hill country of Ephraim and came to Micah’s house.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7007W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7007W\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the five men who had spied out the land of Laish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7008X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7008X\"></sup> said to their fellow Danites, “Do you know that one of these houses has an ephod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7008Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7008Y\"></sup> some household gods and an image overlaid with silver?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7008Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7008Z\"></sup> Now you know what to do.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they turned in there and went to the house of the young Levite at Micah’s place and greeted him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The six hundred Danites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7010AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7010AA\"></sup> armed for battle, stood at the entrance of the gate.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The five men who had spied out the land went inside and took the idol, the ephod and the household gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7011AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7011AB\"></sup> while the priest and the six hundred armed men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7011AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7011AC\"></sup> stood at the entrance of the gate.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When the five men went into Micah’s house and took<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7012AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7012AD\"></sup> the idol, the ephod and the household gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7012AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7012AE\"></sup> the priest said to them, “What are you doing?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They answered him, “Be quiet!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7013AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7013AF\"></sup> Don’t say a word. Come with us, and be our father and priest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7013AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7013AG\"></sup> Isn’t it better that you serve a tribe and clan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7013AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7013AH\"></sup> in Israel as priest rather than just one man’s household?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The priest was very pleased. He took the ephod, the household gods and the idol and went along with the people.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Putting their little children, their livestock and their possessions in front of them, they turned away and left.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When they had gone some distance from Micah’s house, the men who lived near Micah were called together and overtook the Danites.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As they shouted after them, the Danites turned and said to Micah, “What’s the matter with you that you called out your men to fight?”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He replied, “You took<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7018AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7018AI\"></sup> the gods I made, and my priest, and went away. What else do I have? How can you ask, ‘What’s the matter with you?’”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The Danites answered, “Don’t argue with us, or some of the men may get angry and attack you, and you and your family will lose your lives.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So the Danites went their way, and Micah, seeing that they were too strong for him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7020AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7020AJ\"></sup> turned around and went back home.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then they took what Micah had made, and his priest, and went on to Laish, against a people at peace and secure.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7021AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7021AK\"></sup> They attacked them with the sword and burned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7021AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7021AL\"></sup> down their city.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7021AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7021AM\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>There was no one to rescue them because they lived a long way from Sidon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7022AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7022AN\"></sup> and had no relationship with anyone else. The city was in a valley near Beth Rehob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7022AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7022AO\"></sup>The Danites rebuilt the city and settled there.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They named it Dan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7023AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7023AP\"></sup> after their ancestor Dan, who was born to Israel—though the city used to be called Laish.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7023AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7023AQ\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>There the Danites set up for themselves the idol, and Jonathan son of Gershom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7024AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7024AR\"></sup> the son of Moses, and his sons were priests for the tribe of Dan until the time of the captivity of the land.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They continued to use the idol Micah had made,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7025AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7025AS\"></sup> all the time the house of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7025AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7025AT\"></sup> was in Shiloh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7025AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7025AU\"></sup>"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>In those days Israel had no king.Now a Levite who lived in a remote area in the hill country of Ephraim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7026A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7026A\"></sup> took a concubine from Bethlehem in Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7026B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7026B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But she was unfaithful to him. She left him and went back to her parents’ home in Bethlehem, Judah. After she had been there four months,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>her husband went to her to persuade her to return. He had with him his servant and two donkeys. She took him into her parents’ home, and when her father saw him, he gladly welcomed him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>His father-in-law, the woman’s father, prevailed on him to stay; so he remained with him three days, eating and drinking,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7029C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7029C\"></sup> and sleeping there.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>On the fourth day they got up early and he prepared to leave, but the woman’s father said to his son-in-law, “Refresh yourself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7030D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7030D\"></sup> with something to eat; then you can go.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the two of them sat down to eat and drink together. Afterward the woman’s father said, “Please stay tonight and enjoy yourself.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7031E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7031E\"></sup>”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when the man got up to go, his father-in-law persuaded him, so he stayed there that night.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>On the morning of the fifth day, when he rose to go, the woman’s father said, “Refresh yourself. Wait till afternoon!” So the two of them ate together.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then when the man, with his concubine and his servant, got up to leave, his father-in-law, the woman’s father, said, “Now look, it’s almost evening. Spend the night here; the day is nearly over. Stay and enjoy yourself. Early tomorrow morning you can get up and be on your way home.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But, unwilling to stay another night, the man left and went toward Jebus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7035F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7035F\"></sup> (that is, Jerusalem), with his two saddled donkeys and his concubine.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When they were near Jebus and the day was almost gone, the servant said to his master, “Come, let’s stop at this city of the Jebusites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7036G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7036G\"></sup> and spend the night.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>His master replied, “No. We won’t go into any city whose people are not Israelites. We will go on to Gibeah.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He added, “Come, let’s try to reach Gibeah or Ramah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7038H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7038H\"></sup> and spend the night in one of those places.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So they went on, and the sun set as they neared Gibeah in Benjamin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7039I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7039I\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>There they stopped to spend the night.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7040J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7040J\"></sup> They went and sat in the city square,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7040K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7040K\"></sup> but no one took them in for the night.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>That evening<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7041L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7041L\"></sup> an old man from the hill country of Ephraim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7041M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7041M\"></sup> who was living in Gibeah (the inhabitants of the place were Benjamites), came in from his work in the fields.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When he looked and saw the traveler in the city square, the old man asked, “Where are you going? Where did you come from?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7042N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7042N\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He answered, “We are on our way from Bethlehem in Judah to a remote area in the hill country of Ephraim where I live. I have been to Bethlehem in Judah and now I am going to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7043O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7043O\"></sup> No one has taken me in for the night.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>We have both straw and fodder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7044P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7044P\"></sup> for our donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7044Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7044Q\"></sup> and bread and wine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7044R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7044R\"></sup> for ourselves your servants—me, the woman and the young man with us. We don’t need anything.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“You are welcome at my house,” the old man said. “Let me supply whatever you need. Only don’t spend the night in the square.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So he took him into his house and fed his donkeys. After they had washed their feet, they had something to eat and drink.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7046S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7046S\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>While they were enjoying themselves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7047T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7047T\"></sup> some of the wicked men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7047U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7047U\"></sup> of the city surrounded the house. Pounding on the door, they shouted to the old man who owned the house, “Bring out the man who came to your house so we can have sex with him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7047V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7047V\"></sup>”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The owner of the house went outside<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7048W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7048W\"></sup> and said to them, “No, my friends, don’t be so vile. Since this man is my guest, don’t do this outrageous thing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7048X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7048X\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Look, here is my virgin daughter,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7049Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7049Y\"></sup> and his concubine. I will bring them out to you now, and you can use them and do to them whatever you wish. But as for this man, don’t do such an outrageous thing.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But the men would not listen to him. So the man took his concubine and sent her outside to them, and they raped her<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7050Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7050Z\"></sup> and abused her<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7050AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7050AA\"></sup> throughout the night, and at dawn they let her go.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>At daybreak the woman went back to the house where her master was staying, fell down at the door and lay there until daylight.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When her master got up in the morning and opened the door of the house and stepped out to continue on his way, there lay his concubine, fallen in the doorway of the house, with her hands on the threshold.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He said to her, “Get up; let’s go.” But there was no answer. Then the man put her on his donkey and set out for home.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When he reached home, he took a knife<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7054AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7054AB\"></sup> and cut up his concubine, limb by limb, into twelve parts and sent them into all the areas of Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7054AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7054AC\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Everyone who saw it was saying to one another, “Such a thing has never been seen or done, not since the day the Israelites came up out of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7055AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7055AD\"></sup> Just imagine! We must do something! So speak up!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7055AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7055AE\"></sup>”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Then all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7056A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7056A\"></sup> from Dan to Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7056B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7056B\"></sup> and from the land of Gilead came together as one<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7056C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7056C\"></sup> and assembled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7056D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7056D\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Mizpah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7056E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7056E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The leaders of all the people of the tribes of Israel took their places in the assembly of God’s people, four hundred thousand men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7057F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7057F\"></sup> armed with swords.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>(The Benjamites heard that the Israelites had gone up to Mizpah.) Then the Israelites said, “Tell us how this awful thing happened.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the Levite, the husband of the murdered woman, said, “I and my concubine came to Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7059G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7059G\"></sup> in Benjamin to spend the night.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7059H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7059H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>During the night the men of Gibeah came after me and surrounded the house, intending to kill me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7060I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7060I\"></sup> They raped my concubine, and she died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7060J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7060J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I took my concubine, cut her into pieces and sent one piece to each region of Israel’s inheritance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7061K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7061K\"></sup> because they committed this lewd and outrageous act<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7061L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7061L\"></sup> in Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now, all you Israelites, speak up and tell me what you have decided to do.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7062M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7062M\"></sup>”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All the men rose up together as one, saying, “None of us will go home. No, not one of us will return to his house.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But now this is what we’ll do to Gibeah: We’ll go up against it in the order decided by casting lots.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7064N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7064N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>We’ll take ten men out of every hundred from all the tribes of Israel, and a hundred from a thousand, and a thousand from ten thousand, to get provisions for the army. Then, when the army arrives at Gibeah in Benjamin, it can give them what they deserve for this outrageous act done in Israel.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So all the Israelites got together and united as one against the city.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7066O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7066O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The tribes of Israel sent messengers throughout the tribe of Benjamin, saying, “What about this awful crime that was committed among you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7067P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7067P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now turn those wicked men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7068Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7068Q\"></sup> of Gibeah over to us so that we may put them to death and purge the evil from Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7068R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7068R\"></sup>”But the Benjamites would not listen to their fellow Israelites.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>From their towns they came together at Gibeah to fight against the Israelites.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>At once the Benjamites mobilized twenty-six thousand swordsmen from their towns, in addition to seven hundred able young men from those living in Gibeah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Among all these soldiers there were seven hundred select troops who were left-handed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7071S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7071S\"></sup> each of whom could sling a stone at a hair and not miss.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Israel, apart from Benjamin, mustered four hundred thousand swordsmen, all of them fit for battle.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Israelites went up to Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7073T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7073T\"></sup> and inquired of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7073U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7073U\"></sup> They said, “Who of us is to go up first<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7073V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7073V\"></sup> to fight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7073W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7073W\"></sup> against the Benjamites?”The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> replied, “Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7073X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7073X\"></sup> shall go first.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The next morning the Israelites got up and pitched camp near Gibeah.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The Israelites went out to fight the Benjamites and took up battle positions against them at Gibeah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The Benjamites came out of Gibeah and cut down twenty-two thousand Israelites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7076Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7076Y\"></sup> on the battlefield that day.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the Israelites encouraged one another and again took up their positions where they had stationed themselves the first day.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The Israelites went up and wept before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7078Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7078Z\"></sup> until evening,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7078AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7078AA\"></sup> and they inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7078AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7078AB\"></sup> They said, “Shall we go up again to fight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7078AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7078AC\"></sup> against the Benjamites, our fellow Israelites?”The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered, “Go up against them.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the Israelites drew near to Benjamin the second day.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>This time, when the Benjamites came out from Gibeah to oppose them, they cut down another eighteen thousand Israelites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7080AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7080AD\"></sup> all of them armed with swords.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then all the Israelites, the whole army, went up to Bethel, and there they sat weeping before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7081AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7081AE\"></sup> They fasted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7081AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7081AF\"></sup> that day until evening and presented burnt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7081AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7081AG\"></sup> and fellowship offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7081AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7081AH\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7081AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7081AI\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the Israelites inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7082AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7082AJ\"></sup> (In those days the ark of the covenant of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7082AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7082AK\"></sup> was there,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>with Phinehas son of Eleazar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7083AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7083AL\"></sup> the son of Aaron, ministering before it.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7083AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7083AM\"></sup> They asked, “Shall we go up again to fight against the Benjamites, our fellow Israelites, or not?”The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> responded, “Go, for tomorrow I will give them into your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7083AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7083AN\"></sup>”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Israel set an ambush<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7084AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7084AO\"></sup> around Gibeah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>They went up against the Benjamites on the third day and took up positions against Gibeah as they had done before.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The Benjamites came out to meet them and were drawn away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7086AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7086AP\"></sup> from the city. They began to inflict casualties on the Israelites as before, so that about thirty men fell in the open field and on the roads—the one leading to Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7086AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7086AQ\"></sup> and the other to Gibeah.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>While the Benjamites were saying, “We are defeating them as before,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7087AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7087AR\"></sup> the Israelites were saying, “Let’s retreat and draw them away from the city to the roads.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>All the men of Israel moved from their places and took up positions at Baal Tamar, and the Israelite ambush charged out of its place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7088AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7088AS\"></sup> on the west of Gibeah.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then ten thousand of Israel’s able young men made a frontal attack on Gibeah. The fighting was so heavy that the Benjamites did not realize<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7089AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7089AT\"></sup> how near disaster was.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7089AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7089AU\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> defeated Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7090AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7090AV\"></sup> before Israel, and on that day the Israelites struck down 25,100 Benjamites, all armed with swords.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then the Benjamites saw that they were beaten.Now the men of Israel had given way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7091AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7091AW\"></sup> before Benjamin, because they relied on the ambush<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7091AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7091AX\"></sup> they had set near Gibeah.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Those who had been in ambush made a sudden dash into Gibeah, spread out and put the whole city to the sword.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7092AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7092AY\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The Israelites had arranged with the ambush that they should send up a great cloud of smoke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7093AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7093AZ\"></sup> from the city,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7093BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7093BA\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and then the Israelites would counterattack.The Benjamites had begun to inflict casualties on the Israelites (about thirty), and they said, “We are defeating them as in the first battle.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7094BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7094BB\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But when the column of smoke began to rise from the city, the Benjamites turned and saw the whole city going up in smoke.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7095BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7095BC\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then the Israelites counterattacked,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7096BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7096BD\"></sup> and the Benjamites were terrified, because they realized that disaster had come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7096BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7096BE\"></sup> on them.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>So they fled before the Israelites in the direction of the wilderness, but they could not escape the battle. And the Israelites who came out of the towns cut them down there.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>They surrounded the Benjamites, chased them and easily overran them in the vicinity of Gibeah on the east.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Eighteen thousand Benjamites fell, all of them valiant fighters.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7099BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7099BF\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>As they turned and fled toward the wilderness to the rock of Rimmon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7100BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7100BG\"></sup> the Israelites cut down five thousand men along the roads. They kept pressing after the Benjamites as far as Gidom and struck down two thousand more.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>On that day twenty-five thousand Benjamite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7101BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7101BH\"></sup> swordsmen fell, all of them valiant fighters.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>But six hundred of them turned and fled into the wilderness to the rock of Rimmon, where they stayed four months.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>The men of Israel went back to Benjamin and put all the towns to the sword, including the animals and everything else they found. All the towns they came across they set on fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7103BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7103BI\"></sup>"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>The men of Israel had taken an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7104A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7104A\"></sup> at Mizpah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7104B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7104B\"></sup> “Not one of us will give<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7104C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7104C\"></sup> his daughter in marriage to a Benjamite.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The people went to Bethel, where they sat before God until evening, raising their voices and weeping bitterly.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel,” they cried, “why has this happened to Israel? Why should one tribe be missing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7106D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7106D\"></sup> from Israel today?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Early the next day the people built an altar and presented burnt offerings and fellowship offerings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7107E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7107E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the Israelites asked, “Who from all the tribes of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7108F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7108F\"></sup> has failed to assemble before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?” For they had taken a solemn oath that anyone who failed to assemble before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Mizpah was to be put to death.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now the Israelites grieved for the tribe of Benjamin, their fellow Israelites. “Today one tribe is cut off from Israel,” they said.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“How can we provide wives for those who are left, since we have taken an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7110G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7110G\"></sup> by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> not to give them any of our daughters in marriage?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then they asked, “Which one of the tribes of Israel failed to assemble before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Mizpah?” They discovered that no one from Jabesh Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7111H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7111H\"></sup> had come to the camp for the assembly.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For when they counted the people, they found that none of the people of Jabesh Gilead were there.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the assembly sent twelve thousand fighting men with instructions to go to Jabesh Gilead and put to the sword those living there, including the women and children.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“This is what you are to do,” they said. “Kill every male<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7114I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7114I\"></sup> and every woman who is not a virgin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7114J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7114J\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They found among the people living in Jabesh Gilead four hundred young women who had never slept with a man, and they took them to the camp at Shiloh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7115K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7115K\"></sup> in Canaan.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the whole assembly sent an offer of peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7116L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7116L\"></sup> to the Benjamites at the rock of Rimmon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7116M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7116M\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the Benjamites returned at that time and were given the women of Jabesh Gilead who had been spared. But there were not enough for all of them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The people grieved for Benjamin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7118N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7118N\"></sup> because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made a gap in the tribes of Israel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the elders of the assembly said, “With the women of Benjamin destroyed, how shall we provide wives for the men who are left?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The Benjamite survivors must have heirs,” they said, “so that a tribe of Israel will not be wiped out.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7120O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7120O\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>We can’t give them our daughters as wives, since we Israelites have taken this oath:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7121P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7121P\"></sup> ‘Cursed be anyone who gives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7121Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7121Q\"></sup> a wife to a Benjamite.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But look, there is the annual festival of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Shiloh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7122R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7122R\"></sup> which lies north of Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7122S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7122S\"></sup>, east of the road that goes from Bethel to Shechem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7122T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7122T\"></sup> and south of Lebonah.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So they instructed the Benjamites, saying, “Go and hide in the vineyards",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and watch. When the young women of Shiloh come out to join in the dancing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7124U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7124U\"></sup> rush from the vineyards and each of you seize one of them to be your wife. Then return to the land of Benjamin.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When their fathers or brothers complain to us, we will say to them, ‘Do us the favor of helping them, because we did not get wives for them during the war. You will not be guilty of breaking your oath because you did not give<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7125V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7125V\"></sup> your daughters to them.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So that is what the Benjamites did. While the young women were dancing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7126W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7126W\"></sup> each man caught one and carried her off to be his wife. Then they returned to their inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7126X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7126X\"></sup> and rebuilt the towns and settled in them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7126Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7126Y\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>At that time the Israelites left that place and went home to their tribes and clans, each to his own inheritance.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In those days Israel had no king; everyone did as they saw fit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7128Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7128Z\"></sup>"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;